The [How to Contribute guide](https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/AMBARI/How+to+Contribute) says PRs can be linked to a related existing JIRA if the change is minor.  (Although I'm not sure I see the value of even that for fixing typos.)

I think you can link to [AMBARI-8454](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMBARI-8454), which introduced the file being changed in this PR.  Or to one of several JIRAs for typos, eg. [AMBARI-18702](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMBARI-18702).

Jenkins is failing when building Ambari Metrics Flume Sink (see https://builds.apache.org/job/Ambari-Github-PullRequest-Builder/126/console); this has nothing to do with my change.
This test -
 org.apache.hadoop.metrics2.sink.flume.FlumeTimelineMetricsSinkTest.testMetricsRetrievalExceptionTolerance - can be executed successfully in my local environment both in CLI and in IDE (10 times out of 10).

Additional information: @adoroszlai indicated that this test used to be non-deterministic in the past (see https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMBARI-22155).

My question is: is it possible to merge my changes regardless the Jenkins build result?
